boolean-condition-13.title: Record created?
boolean-condition-13.description: The synchronization is only done at record creation.

boolean-condition-15.title: Is xedit?
boolean-condition-15.description: xedit is an update with the daily job that changes Platinum Customer, Has Active Subscriptions and ARRs. We don't want to sync customer to SF to this records because only one field is updated and the other fields are not returned by the script.

boolean-condition-4.title: Delete old record?
boolean-condition-4.description:
The old record must be deleted:
- for an edition, if the customer or the class was changed.
- for an deletion.

boolean-condition-5.title: Upsert new record?
boolean-condition-5.description:
The new record must be:
- inserted for a creation.
- updated for an edit.

boolean-condition-9.title: Matches actual NS realm?
boolean-condition-9.description: Returns true if the new/old record are from the expected NS realm; else, returns false.

call-workflow-10.title: Sync to Zendesk
call-workflow-10.description: Sync to Zendesk the fields Active Subscription and Platinum Customer

call-workflow-9.title: Trigger Sync NS Quote to SF
call-workflow-9.description: Calls asynchronously the subflow for syncing the NS quote into Salesforce.

script-1.title: Get expected NS realm
script-1.description:
Determines the expected NS realm based on the workflow title.
If the workflow title starts with "[full]", then return "4914352_SB2"; else, return "4914352".

terminate-1.title: Skip any unexpected NS realm
terminate-1.description: Skips all triggers from any unexpected NS realm.
